The paper deals with unsupervised learning on neural network outputs, specifically a deep Convolutional Neural Network trained on the ImageNet of 1000 classes. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new zero-shot learning method, which involves using the visual features learned by PCA/ICA. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with interpreting the PCA/ICA components as common visual features shared by similar object classes, which suggests that it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper may also belong to the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category, as it deals with analyzing the outputs of a neural network.
